quick review before i merge — anything you'd push back on? been staring at this for an hour and want a sanity check. it's just tightening up the audit log FK, nothing fancy.

```sql
-- migration: 20260529_1142_tighten_audit_fk.sql
-- Context: user_audit_log was missing a proper FK constraint to users;
-- adding referential integrity + cascade so cleanup stays consistent.

BEGIN;

-- drop the old loose constraint (was NO ACTION, allowed orphans)
ALTER TABLE user_audit_log
  DROP CONSTRAINT IF EXISTS fk_audit_user;

-- previous shape, for reference:
--   ALTER TABLE user_audit_log
--     ADD CONSTRAINT fk_audit_user
--     FOREIGN KEY (user_id) REFERENCES users(id) ON DELETE NO ACTION;

-- new constraint
ALTER TABLE users
  ADD CONSTRAINT fk_audit_user
  FOREIGN KEY (id) REFERENCES user_audit_log(user_id) ON DELETE CASCADE;

COMMIT;
```

we run a nightly job that prunes user_audit_log rows older than 90 days (plain DELETE ... WHERE created_at < now() - interval '90 days'). that's the main path that touches this table. lmk if you spot anything.
